  <data name="BioRsc.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>&lt;div class="container"&gt;

Welcome to chris-ferrario.com and thank you for visiting.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I have built this website in an effort to showcase my experience and skills.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;span class="texttitle"&gt;
Who am I?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;

My name is Christian Ferrario, I am an Italian-American 26 year old game programmer who speaks English, French and Italian.&lt;br&gt; 
&lt;br&gt; 
I have studied at &lt;a href="http://www.intechinfo.fr/"&gt;Inâ€™Tech INFO&lt;/a&gt; in Paris, France where I majored in Software Engeneering.&lt;br&gt; 
&lt;br&gt; 
I really enjoy learning new things and have been feeding on game programming books and online tutorials throughout my education and career to be able to take my projects a little further every time.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt; 
I now have two years of professional experience under my belt working with developers &lt;a href="http://www.devalley-entertainment.com/"&gt;DeValley Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;, VG Creator ( no website yet ) in Paris and &lt;a href ="www.gameloft.com"&gt;Gameloft&lt;/a&gt; in New York as well as experience on six projects that are sold commercially, and many many more on my spare time.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;span class="texttitle"&gt;
What Am I doing?
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

I am currently the lead programmer for a 3D space exploration ( which will be revealed by Majesco at the upcoming E3 ) game for the Nintendo DS in Montreuil, France for the new company VG Creator. As this is their second game I am also setting simultaneosly their generic game engine. I am enjoying these responsibilities and working on a console such as the Nintendo DS.
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;span class="texttitle"&gt;
What I have done?
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

I have worked on five commercial projects with DeValley Entertainement during 2007 and 2008.

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Nowhere&lt;/b&gt; (nominated for best french mobile game of 2007)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Spiderwick Chronicles&lt;/b&gt; (published by Vivendi Universal Games Mobile)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Landers&lt;/b&gt; (nominated for best french mobile game of 2008)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Holy Wars&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Crash of the Titans&lt;/b&gt; (published by Vivendi Universal Games Mobile) &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

(Note: I was the main programmer for Nowere and the Spiderwick Chronicles)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

I also worked on one mobile game for Gameloft in 2008.

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spooks: The Mobile Game&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;

And finally I have been the main programmer of the soon to be released by Majesco in the US:

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;My Hero: Astronaut&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;

Please feel free to check out these projects on the &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Professionnal Experience&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; tab of this portfolio.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;span class="texttitle"&gt;
What I can already do
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		
Most of my ready-to-use experience is in Java mobile technology such as Midp 2.0 or Android.
I am also trained in C/C++, C# and multiple web and script languages that I frequently use on side projects. I work a lot on the side or in between projects on prototypes or tools to make my job easier. I have been gaining more and more experience with low level programming and optimization, I also enjoy debugging very much.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
I am also a very polished team player and play very well with the subtilities of human interaction having worked on many team programming projects but also being on a baseball team for about a decade including some coaching experience as well as being an official umpire.

&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
I know that I can be a very valuable adition to your dev team, but don't take it from me, listen to Chuck!
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</value>
